ng</i>. This name has been assimilated to the patronymic surname in Devon from Sir John Hawkyns (1532–95), victor against the Spanish Armada (1588), who was a member of the Devon family of <i>Hawkins</i>, a branch of a Kentish family from the village of Hawkinge. They held land in Plymouth as long ago as 1480.","Irish: variant of   Haughn  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Hawkin","meanings":["English: variant of   Hawken  ."]}]},{"name":"Sarah","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, borne by the wife of Abraham and mother of Isaac. According to the Book of Genesis, she was originally called <i>Sarai</i> (possibly meaning ‘contentious’ in Hebrew), but had her name changed by God to the more auspicious <i>Sarah</i> ‘princess’ in token of a greater blessing (Genesis 17:15, ‘And God said unto Abraham, As for Sarai thy wife, thou shalt not call her name Sarai, but Sarah shall her name be’). This has been one of the most enduringly popular girls' names."],"variants":[{"name":"Sara","meanings":["Variant of   Sarah .  This is the form used in the Greek of the New Testament (Hebrews 11:11)."]}]},{"name":"Anna","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["variant of   Anne  , in common use as a given name in most European languages. Among people with a classical education, it has from time to time been associated with  Virgil's  Aeneid, where it is borne by the sister of  Dido , Queen of Carthage. This Phoenician name may ultimately be of Semitic origin, and thus related to the biblical <i>Anne</i>. However, the connection, if it exists, is indirect rather than direct."],"variants":[{"name":"Anne","meanings":["A name corrpted from Hannah, q.v. It is also found several times in a male name. From Ann, Anne, we have as nicknames Nan and Nancy"]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Sarah Anna Hawkins 10 ggm was born in 1507, in Bocking, Essex, England, United Kingdom. She married Matthew Mathei Whipple I 10 ggf on 7 May 1522, in Bocking, Essex, England. She died in 1542, in Braintree, Essex, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 35."},"et":{"1507–1542":"1507–1542","1505–1547":"1505–1547","1523–1549":"1523–1549","1547":"1547","1523":"1523","1542":"1542","7 May 1522":"7. mai 1522","1507":"1507","1527":"1527","1549":"1549","1505":"1505","Braintree, Braintree district, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Braintree, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bocking, Essex, England":"Bocking, Essex, England","Bocking, Braintree district, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Bocking, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"1507–1542":"1507–1542","1505–1547":"1505–1547","1523–1549":"1523–1549","1547":"1547","1523":"1523","1542":"1542","7 May 1522":"7. toukokuuta 1522","1507":"1507","1527":"1527","1549":"1549","1505":"1505","Braintree, Braintree district, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Braintree, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bocking, Essex, England":"Bocking, Essex, England","Bocking, Braintree district, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Bocking, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England"},"fr":{"1507–1542":"1507–1542","1505–1547":"1505–1547","1523–1549":"1523–1549","1547":"1547","1523":"1523","1542":"1542","7 May 1522":"7 mai 1522","1507":"1507","1527":"1527","1549":"1549","1505":"1505","Braintree, Braintree district, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Braintree, Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Bocking, Essex, England":"Bocking, Essex, Angleterre","Bocking, Braintree district, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Bocking, Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Sarah Anna Hawkins 10 ggm est née en 1507, à Bocking, Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Matthew Mathei Whipple I 10 ggf le 7 mai 1522, à Bocking, Essex, Angleterre. Elle est décédée en 1542, à Braintree, Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 35 ans."},"de":{"1